article.headline: Butler 64, Green Bay 62
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Matt Howard scored 22 points and Butler edged Wisconsin-Green Bay 64-62 on Tuesday night. Shelvin Mack added 13 points and Shawn Vanzant had 12 for the Bulldogs (19-9, 11-5 Horizon), who have won five straight. Rahmon Fletcher led the Phoenix (12-15, 6-9) with 18 points, and Alec Brown had 12. Butler went into halftime up 34-28 but was unable to pull away as Green Bay, which never led after intermission, stayed within eight points the entire second half.
